<h1>Get started</h1>

<p>While this tool streamlines installation of the modules, it should be installed.</p>

<h2>Installation</h2>

<p>In your PowerShell console execute:</p>

<pre><code>(new-object Net.WebClient).DownloadString("http://psget.net/GetPsGet.ps1") | iex</code></pre>

<p>You are done. This nice line of PowerShell script will dowload <code>GetPsGet.ps1</code> and send it to <code>Invoke-Expression</code> to install PsGet Module.</p>

<p>Alternativelly you can do installation manually</p>
<ol>
    <li>Download <code>PsGet.psm1</code> from <a href="https://github.com/chaliy/psget/">https://github.com/chaliy/psget/</a></li>
	<li>Copy <code>PsGet.psm1</code> to your modules folder (e.g. <code>Modules\PsGet\</code> )</li>
	<li>Execute <code>Import-Module PsGet</code> (or add this to your profile)</li>
	<li>Enjoy!</li>
</ol>

